name: integer_u32_binary32_exact_boundary
description: |
  This is 2^24. Binary32 represents it exactly, but the spacing between
  adjacent representable values becomes 2 at this magnitude. It is therefore
  exact itself but is the first positive integer beyond the all-integers-exact
  range.
format: hex
decode-as: u32
pair:
  - with: binary32-first-lost-integer.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "integer"
  - "unsigned-integer"
  - "u32"
  - "binary32"
  - "float-roundtrip"
  - "unsafe-integer"
  - "precision"
  - "boundary"
---
00 00 00 01 # 16777216 (2^24)
